Where are the prisoners of the Freeport Militia held?


>From: "CybrWzrd" <CybrWzrd@...>
>Reply-To: eqpaladin@onelist.com
>To: <eqpaladin@onelist.com>
>Subject: [eqpaladin] Zimel's Blades
>Date: Thu, 3 Jun 1999 16:06:51 -0500
>
>The quest regarding Zimel has officially been noted as broken by the GM's
>as of late, but i have found yet another clue regarding this Holy Sword
>quest. I recently spoke with a prisoner of the Freeport Milita, appatently
>he has been beaten or drugged senseless, but When I mentioned the name of
>the infamous Zimel to him, he looked deep into my eyes with understanding (
>A prisoner gazes deep into your eyes (kinda eerie) When I mentioned the
>Sword of his Creation, this prisoner said something gutteral, his words
>were "nnnn... Girkle.... Grunk.... Shoo Bog n' Goo". He did not respond to
>anything else, only the name Zimel and the sword Soulfire. Maybe we are all
>going the wrong way in the search for Zimel, maybe the one underground is A
>fake.... and Maybe if you kill the Prison guards....
>
>Also in my Travels for the Test of truth, I gave a tunic to Altunic, and he
>said that I was too weak for him to talk to me.....
>
>Laurana Highwind
>Paladin of the 21st Rank
>List mediator
